name: Random Mod

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "Do me a favor and just look into that Pyramidion thing, would you?  If the Vex are studying the best of humanity, you know they've got stuff on me in there.” —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "Gotta love the views on Io. I remember watching Jupiter float over the horizon, all big and stormy. I left a cache up there, and… fell asleep. Next thing I know, my Ghost's reviving me at the base of the cliff. Guess I roll around in my sleep.” —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "Bear with me. I have this memory on Io where I was just sniping Vex from a ledge. Then the sky went dark, and man, I can't remember anything but pain and running and calling for an evac. I know I left something behind on that one." —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "Asher called me to rant about a Taken Blight destroying a research wing of the Cabal base, and I'm like, why are you telling me? We're not friends; and then he mentions seeing one of my caches in the debris. Survived a Taken Blight. Not a bad design, if I do say so myself." —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "Damn Rhinos. Made off with everything from my lockers when they ransacked the Tower. This one here, they dragged to Io and apparently left it behind. Last ping I got came from their abandoned base on the Echo Mesa." —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "The lead I got from Asher was some Psion was seen making off with this one somewhere in the Echo Mesa. He mumbled something about it being on top of some Cabal checkpoint, before it—well—fell into a pit of Taken. And we all know how that turns out." —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "You ever talk to Banshee much? He's got this saying: Sometime the deeper you go, the less you'll ever understand. The Cabal are kind of like that. Why they feel the need to drag my stuff into their damn Io base… beyond me." —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "OK, another live cache report here… Gotta give the Cabal credit. They're great at digging tunnels. Then again, so are worms… and snakes… and woodchucks… and crabs... and ants… ugh, I hate ants." —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "OK, so, Albios's memorial service was on Io. Sacred to Warlocks, blah blah blah. Don't get me wrong, I liked Al—but the service ran a bit long. Ended up betting Banshee I could make a few hairy jumps high up on the Mesa. Broke both my legs, but I did it. I forget what Banshee gave me, but I know I left it in a cache up there somewhere.” —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "So word is one of the Cabal's drill engineers found another one of my caches. I don't know if I did such a good job sealing it or if those dumb rhino fingers are too fat to pry it open. Anyway, it's been spotted in some hole near that drill site. I guess Ghaul called them back before they could get into it." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "Thought I'd escaped, but you know how the Vex are. I got as far as this energy shield, thinking it was a way out. Dead end. So I dropped what I had there and tried to shoot through. Bam! Right back into the loop.”

name: Nessus Treasure Map

Anyway, I got the cache, then got a tiny bit turned around and ended up in a Cabal base. You know how that is. The dogs and all. Had to stash the goods quickly and get out. So… can you go get it?” —Cayde-6

description: "So this cache… I don't know. It seemed like a good idea at the time. How do you feel about climbing trees?" —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "So down I went. I thought maybe the deeper it got, the better access I would have to their core Mind or Nexus points. I do read Ikora's Vex reports. Sometimes. Anyway, found nothing but roots." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "I guess I was afraid that Mind juice would somehow seize control of my weapons or something. That stuff isn't some kind of luxurious milk bath, trust me." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "I was just doing what Failsafe said. I mean, she seems reliable, half the time. So I entered this cave and set up my little fallback point, took a few steps in, and bam, the battle began." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "One point, I thought I'd broken free, so I made a break for a path through a tangle of roots. Caught sight of the cache and then bam, I was back in the loop again." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "Of course, I didn't go charging into Nessus without a plan. I made sure I had caches everywhere. Started with the first dead Vex construct I found." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "I don't know what they call it. The eyeball thing. Under that. You'll know it when you see it." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "It was like I was being called closer, like something wanted my help. Then I get to this tower with a triangular doorway and go through. That's when it got really weird." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "I wonder if the Vex even realize I hide stuff between the gaps in their block networks. Hmmm. Maybe that's how they know so much about me." —Cayde-6

name: Nessus Treasure Map
description: "Good news: I left myself a reminder note for this cache! Bad news: the note says ‘Whatever you do, under any circumstances, do not look down.' That's enough to go on, right?”

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "OK, all I can give you to go on in this one is… it's high up. So… look up, I guess? Don't look at me like that, I'm doing my best.” —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "I've been all around this system, seen all sorts of transports, but nothing with the resiliency of this old Golden Age rustbucket I found in the EDZ. Used it as a grab-and-go spot for years." —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "I used to have this old lookout. Scoped out my first FWC bunker there. Just like the Cabal to plop that eyesore of a base right on top of a piece of dark age nostalgia. Do me a favor, if you make it up there: snipe a few rhinos for me." —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "I tell you what. You get to work cleaning out the angry spider-pirates and space-rhinos, and I give you the deed to this little cabin I won from Ren. With a little work, could become a nice little getaway." —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "So I took off edging the cliff, Golden Gun down to one shot. Left a lot behind cliffside. Bad day." —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "So after a full day of pulling loot out of the Fallen's hands, I thought I would just cool my engines down by that old river, but as soon as I cached it all up down there, a Servitor shows up." —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "You know, I used to think if it's marked a dead zone, it's my kind of place. Vanguard cured me of that, but I left plenty behind there back in the day. Third-floor balcony, above the alley.  Loved that spot…. Hope the Fallen haven't got to it." —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "You do much driving? Me neither. But I used to spend nights hiding out near this truck just teetering on a ledge, just waiting for the day some dumb Dreg would send it over the ledge. That day never came." —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "This place is full of old containers. Don't bother raiding them all—I already did. They're all filled with shoes. Mountains of Golden Age footwear, and not a thing in my size." —Cayde-6

name: EDZ Treasure Map
description: "So once you get up there, don't be afraid to strut it on the catwalk. We both know the importance of looking good." —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "I got word on another cache in the Echo Mesa. Some of Asher's 'assistants' chased a Legionary out of the Cabal Base but lost him in a little cave nearby. Must've left it there, since the rhino came out empty handed. That's when the assistants got him. Good thing, 'cause I'd rather it go to you." —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "You know Eris Morn, right? Creepy three-eyed old Hunter, too much foundation? Doesn't matter. She comes in and asks me how Io was and I say, wrong Vanguard, ask Ikora; and she's like, I was hoping that cache by the bones marked your grave; and I'm like, I'm an Exo, I left my bones behind a long time ago; and she goes, exactly. You get anything from that?" —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "Have you ever had a dream you're in this cave full of mist and you see this amazing cache, but every time you reach to open it, a new layer of mists blocks your path? No? Am I the only one who has this dream?" —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "When I was caught in that Vex Teleporter, I would end up in weird places. Once or twice, I swear it was Io and saw one of my own caches on top one of those tall, pointy Vex things. That's all I got for you. That ‘porter was not a fun time!” —Cayde-6

name: Io Treasure Map
description: "Funny thing, I know I've been to Io, but all the details are pretty hazy. Guess I'm getting old.  I have this memory of a battle on a bridge. Vex everywhere. After crossing a bridge, we took cover to the right, and then, well, it gets fuzzy from there. Maybe worth checking out?" —Cayde-6
